==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin '''[[electricus|ēlectricus]]''' "made of amber", from {{AGr.}}  '''{{polytonic|[[ἤλεκτρον]]}}''' (ēlektron) "amber", related to '''{{polytonic|[[ἠλέκτωρ]]}}''' (ēlektor) "shining sun"

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ɪˈlɛktɹɪk/}}, {{SAMPA|/I"lEktrIk/}}
*{{audio|en-us-electric.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Of, relating to, produced by, operated with, or utilising [[electricity]]; [[electrical]].
# Of, or relating to an [[electronic]] version of a [[musical instrument]] that has an [[acoustic]] equivalent.
# Being [[emotionally]] [[thrilling]]; [[electrifying]].

